snippet.textDisplay:
lol in a work environment why would you ever want to put an 8 TB drive on a machine? You're just inviting the dumb dumbs to store their work locally except on the server were it belongs and its backed up every day. Unless they need it none of my guys get more than 256 GB of memory cause that's the cheapest solution for a fast drive. I used 128 GB in the past but I've found for allot of users that's not a lot of scratch space room after installing all the software.
In a work for yourself environment...I guess but you better have a backup drive through USB and once a week at least backing that data off site. I've seen too many cases were people spend all their money to get that huge storage solution and then come to me for advice when it fails....maybe you should have spent less on that huge drive and instead spent some money on a backup solution and a way to archive old data off site? I laugh in their faces except I feel sorry for them when I tell them how much it's going to cost to send it to someone for data recovery. Then all of a sudden a backup solution looks very economical. lol I get being cheap but people are always cheap in the wrong places when it comes to computers.
